SIMPLE: ringlet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ringlet
<hw>Ring"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ring</ets> +
<ets>-let</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small ring; a small circle;
specifically, a fairy ring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You demi-puppets, that⟦br⟧
By moonshine do the green sour <qex>ringlets</qex> make,⟦br⟧
Whereof the ewe not bites.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A curl; especially, a curl of hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Her golden tresses] in wanton <qex>ringlets</qex> waved.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ringman</ent>⟦br⟧
